Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 13:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix mobile Safari layout issue with conditional container and width

The original mobile Safari layout bug was caused by the interplay of
`shrink-0`, an inline `width: 100%`, and the `@container` utility on
the session side panel. On small screens Safari calculated the flex
item's width incorrectly, resulting in the panel occupying roughly 40%
of the screen instead of stretching across the full width.

This patch implements a robust fix that preserves desktop behaviour
while ensuring the panel occupies the full width on mobile:

* The `@container` utility is now applied only on desktop (`isDesktop()`),
  so container queries still work where they are needed but no longer
  interfere with width calculations on small screens.
* The `shrink-0` class is applied conditionally when running on
  desktop **and** the side panel is open. Mobile no longer has a
  hard-coded shrink constraint.
* The panel now always includes `w-full` alongside `flex-1` to
  explicitly occupy the full width on mobile.
* The inline style now omits a width on mobile (uses `undefined`),
  preventing Safari from misinterpreting `width: 100%` in flex
  contexts. On desktop the width still comes from
  `sessionPanelWidth()`.

Desktop functionality (collapsible side panel and container queries)
remains unchanged because the conditional classes mirror the prior
behaviour on larger screens. On mobile, the panel now reliably
expands to occupy the available space.

--- a/packages/app/src/pages/session.tsx
+++ b/packages/app/src/pages/session.tsx
@@
         <div
           classList={{
-            "@container relative shrink-0 flex flex-col min-h-0 h-full bg-background-stronger": true,
-            "flex-1": true,
-            "w-full md:flex-none": desktopSidePanelOpen(),
-            "hidden md:flex": !isDesktop() && store.mobileTab === "changes",
+            // Always use relative positioning and flex column with minimum height.
+            "relative flex flex-col min-h-0 h-full bg-background-stronger": true,
+            // Ensure the panel fills available space and spans the full width on mobile.
+            "flex-1 w-full": true,
+            // Apply container queries only on desktop to avoid Safari sizing bugs on mobile.
+            "@container": isDesktop(),
+            // Prevent shrinking only on desktop when the side panel is open.
+            "shrink-0": isDesktop() && desktopSidePanelOpen(),
+            // Maintain flex-none on desktop to allow the panel to collapse correctly when open.
+            "md:flex-none": desktopSidePanelOpen(),
+            // Hide on mobile when the changes tab is active; on desktop the panel remains visible.
+            "hidden md:flex": !isDesktop() && store.mobileTab === "changes",
           }}
           style={{
-            width: isDesktop() ? sessionPanelWidth() : "100%",
+            // Only set an explicit width on desktop. On mobile, undefined prevents Safari miscalculation.
+            width: isDesktop() ? sessionPanelWidth() : undefined,
           }}